Properties of JS       = Every language comes with it’s unique set of features. 

Javascript has the following -

1. Interpreted        =  JavaScript is an interpreted language, meaning it's executed line-by-line at runtime by the JavaScript engine in the browser or server environment, rather than being compiled into machine code beforehand.

Upsides(pros) - There is one less step to do before running your code (very easy steps to run the code)

Downsides(cons) - Performance Overhead, More prone to runtime errors (downside of js performance are slow, its have a lot have compilation  during run time,ofc slow compile,bcz of lots of checks pass )

2. Dynamically Typed   =  Variables in JavaScript are not bound to a specific data type. Types are determined at runtime and can change as the program executes
