3. Single threaded     = JavaScript executes code in a single-threaded environment, meaning it processes one task at a time. We will dive deeper into this next week.

4. Garbage collected   = JavaScript automatically manages memory allocation and deallocation through garbage collection, which helps prevent memory leaks by automatically reclaiming memory used by objects no longer in use.

